article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- — Jeremy Lorenz scored 16 points as Wofford beat Gardner-Webb 88-64 on Wednesday night. Lorenz shot 7 for 8, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc for the Terriers (4-5). Kyler Filewich scored 15 points while shooting 7 of 11 from the field and added nine rebounds. Corey Tripp shot 6 for 11, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 14 points. Jamaine Mann led the Runnin' Bulldogs (4-5) in scoring, finishing with 15 points. Jacob Hudson added 14 points for Gardner-Webb. Colin Hawkins had nine points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
